caption: Disappointed!  Food was tasty but the staff forgot to give me some of my sides.  Had to change from 4 stars to 5 stars because the food was amazing!!!! So tasty!

You've heard the saying, first impression  counts well is sure did love there food on the first go around but the second kinda through me for a loop my chicken was not all the way done it could have cooked a little bit more but let me explain the first time I went it was a family my mom and I just waiting but the second it was packed now I think that's what played a difference but they are amazing just being honest

Professional and pleasant staff. Although I specifically asked for extra sauce on my jerk chicken and didn't get any sauce at all, it was well seasoned. I wasn't prepared for the spicy Mac n Cheese. All in all good food.
Food is good. simply the worst service
Had the Rasta Pasta !!! Speechless!!! I was trying to save some for later but that didn't happen. Lol Also the Reflection drink was deliciou! Worth the wait for sure!

Oxtail was tender and properly spicy, but WAY TOO SALTY.  Like 3x what was needed.  In looking at Yelp reviews afterwards, I am not alone on this.  Too bad as I was looking forward to making this a regular treat.
Worth the wait on a cold Friday night!

Good food but the line on a Friday night is crazy!!! I don’t know what’s the point of taking our orders on the ticket and then we still have to stand in line for 1-2 hours to pay. It’s ridiculous. They need come up with a more efficient way to take orders faster.
I LOVE LOVE LOVE the chicken Tacos!!!!😋😋

The food taste good but the cabbage was crunchier than chips and the chicken was tough. Plantains was the only thing that was fully cooked in my opinion. I will go back because I like the taste of the food but I don't like tough meat. I'll take  the crunchy cabbage before I do the meat. Jerk combo with jerk pasta extra soft bread

Rasta pasta the best wish they where open more I took my baby daddy and he loved it

caption: This place indisputably has thee worst Jamaican food I've yet to eat.  The rice and peas were heavily inundated with what tasted like barbeque sauce.  The jerk chicken was a joke chicken:  not authentic Jamaican spice.  The cabbage was too overly cooked to be considered Jamaican.  A sheer disappointment over all.  To the Respondent:  I shared my assessment.  Glad you're blessed and glad you're going to work on your brand.  No shade on my end.  Just honesty on my part.
Got the oxtail  didn't really like them had a sweet taste to them which I didn't like rice and peas were cooked ok
The jerk chicken and rasta pasta are a go-to and they never disappoint. The recipe is consistent!
Delicious 😋

The chicken nachos were bomb but the meatless thing was trash. Cabbage was good tho. Could really eat only the cabbage...  Oh and don’t forget all them bones in the bean and rice... BRO!!!! Don’t do that. I almost choked on the sh**.. wash the meat better . Wash them bones out !!!!!
I admire this venue very much. there is a friendly ambiance. The meals are great. the service is dynamic and the stuff is very professional. The cost is honest. very much recommend.

I really hate to give this business one star; however, it was not good and made me sick. I paid $28 for the  platter and was very disappointed by the small portion size. I got the  chicken and salmon. I had to discard my chicken because the skin on the quarter breast was covered in feathers and the chicken leg was not cooked to the bone. The mac and cheese just tasted like uncooked seasoning. The rice and salmon were extremely salty...almost inedible. It gave me a headache. I became nauseous not long after eating the food.

Seen a lot of bad reviews. I don't like my food over powered with spicy flavors.  Also people should be allowed to choose between mild or spicy for a number of reason health being number one.  So i won't be goin here.  Honestly Jamaican food in the D.M.V is gone down hill.

I previously ordered from them using door dash. First of all they forgot  my whole meal platter and secondly they were out of beef patties and didn’t call instead decided to leave this note in my bag saying “ enjoy extra Mac, no more beef patty”. You don’t do that trifling stuff! You give someone a call and ask if that’s what they would prefer. I have a picture of the note and will be posting. I tried to post the pic but it won’t let me but trust me I will Never deal with this trifling mess again.
The best jerk chicken tacos you may have to wait if you dont order online and parking is limited
Amazing!!!!!

So I’ve come down to this place 5 times in the last month now and every time their oxtails are sold out and the employees have told me different times to come down to catch them and each time I come down they are sold out. My thing is if you know your TOP SELLER (apparently) is oxtails and that particular food is always sold out by a certain time than start doubling up. Working people like me can’t make it to the place by 4/5 pm. Start making sure that you have enough to serve the late evening working people that can’t pull up Until 7/8pm you should not be running out of food 4 hours after you open. Again 5 times I’ve  tried to catch them for a certain food, NO LUCK!!!  Please if you want oxtails after a certain time than this is not the place to go. #Respectfully
This food is soooo good!! Truly the best Jamaican I’ve had in the DMV area.
Love the video here!!! recommend the jerk tocos and pasta😩❤️
Love the genre of food. I can't wait until their open Everyday ❣️❣️❣️🤎
First time going last night and it was amazing 👍🏾 They need to fix their Google times though. Friday says 8pm on Google but they close at 7 on Fridays smh
The food was extremely spicy in everything taste the same. I was expecting better
Even though this is a food truck it has some of the best Caribbean food around. Jerk mac and cheese is a YUM
That was good. Get the bread and try the jerk combo
Maybe I just got a bad batch.  My tacos tasted like a pure salt taco.  My blood pressure went into overdrive.  I’m still nursing a headache 2 days later.
Excellent food when it's good, but lately sometimes when I deliver it's off. New chef?
Lawd the jerk the Mac and cheese!! I can’t wait to go back 🥰😍😍

I ordered the jerk chicken wing platter with rice ,cabbage , mac & cheese and the oxtail Platter with rice and cabbage. The food was amazing; the only thing was the cabbage had too much pepper in it. My husband said this is his go to spot for now on and I agree.
Food was great as always

This is not Jamaican Food! It’s hot sauce and ketchup that’s cooked by non-Jamaicans, who could at-lest try to get a more authentic taste by hiring some Caribbean chefs to teach them how the food actually should be prepared. I apologize for the honesty but the food needs work.
On my first visit, I was the only customer in line on a Sunday and I was rushed. On top of the that the chicken was not fresh.
Best food I’ve ever had!!!!!!

I passed this place randomly walking by. First, and most importantly, it's very, VERY, spicy. I didn't know that before buying, however it was very good. Make sure to grab a water. I don't normally like spicy food, but it was still delicious. I would go again and jusr try something a little milder. Service was great and lined moved along smoothly for a Saturday night with Covid protocols in place. I do wish there was somewhere to eat, like chairs or a table so keep that in mind when coming. It is strictly take out. I would recommend for a late night out eat.
The food looks delicious but it’s over seasoned and made me and my partner very sick. Not sure if it was just an off day but I’m not giving them another chance.
Best nachos I ever had in my life! Go there on the regular for them (jerk chicken nachos). Every other item is amazing as well! True Jamaican flavors.
Really great mac&cheese
Can you say bomb

Man I love jamaican food and never disappointed.
Excellent place to buy something when in a rush. Their service is quick, prices are affordable, excellent atmosphere. I highly recommend this place
Excellent prices and portions pictured is the Jerk Nachos
Jerk Chicken and Jerck Mac and Cheese are really good

I had di Yaadie (jerk chicken beans and rice and cabbage) at the food truck and the food was great. The presentation looked great. Crisp vegetables, an abundance of spices with flavors. I left off a star for texture preferences. I prefer grilled/ smoked jerk chicken that is juicy and tender like was seen in sweet mangoes. However I think the chicken was baked / broiled. Also I prefer my cabbage to be somewhat crisp. Even still it all tasted good, decent price point and great portions.👍🏾

Easily the best food truck in DC and some of the best Jamaican fusion food I've had period. The quality of customer service is also great, especially considering how long the lines are consistently. I look forward to when their restaurant opens in the near future.
Closed too early...food...Ive had better
Food is terrible
If you like spicy food please go it's not for the weak at all !!! The chicken is moist and tender 😭😋 the Mac n cheese is great I highly recommend you try the jerk chicken with rice and peas & cabbage

I had been following them for a whole year. I finally had them today & im very disappointed. Everything was spicy. No flavor just SPICY. How do you make Mac and cheese spicy? Like really. And the cabbage? And the salmon? And the chicken? It’s really no flavor just spice. I’m very disappointed. I really expected to be hooked but tbh I’m so sad I wasted $45.
Everything is great!!! I love the salmon and chicken. My favorite sides are the Mac and cabbage , and black owned ! Can’t beat it.
Best Jamaican food in the DMV. Got the Rasta Pasta and Jerk Salmon and both dishes were amazing. Going back for the Jerk Tacos 😋

Very delicious food! Supported for quite sometime and I’m in love with the food! I cannot wait for their location at 1100 H Street NE to open. Whenever I need quality food made with care,  I’m going to Jerk At Nite!!
Great customer service and food was delicious! Emily was an amazing cashier.
Not only are they alumni awwwww HU! The food is full of flavor and portion sizes match the price! I’m so addicted I have my whole squad rocking with them too.
I LOVE the food here. Great jerk chicken & Mac.

The young lady taking the orders poor customer service. When you are working durning a world pandemic and someone comes to support a small business and comes politely you should give the same respect. The food was COLD. Good size portions. I will not return.
Out of Oxtails when I got there, but the customer service and speed of service was on point!  One love Jerk At Nite! ☝🏾❤️ 🇯🇲
Listen this is the best Jerk food in the dmv! The Rasta pasta has to be my favorite with the jerk mac omg! Seasoning next level
When I say they are they bestttttt your taste buds will thank me later.... Everything is 🔥🔥🔥 hands down!!
The food tastes as though it’s made with LOVE! There is a little wait sometimes but GREAT things are worth waiting for!
Their jerk Mac and cheese is out of this world! It’s a party in my mouth and I’m invited! I invite you to the same taste party in your mouth!
Quick, Tasty, and inexpensive! When they’re is a wait it’s still worth the wait!
Jerk @ Nite is a whole experience for your taste buds!!! I highly recommend the jerk salmon, Mac and cheese, oxtails, or anything on the menu for that matter!!!! The best Jamaican food in DC!!!

I was very hesitant about trying Jerk@nite because so many Caribbean style eateries are so disappointing in the DMV. I had the oxtails with rice and cabbage and it was a flavorful but small portion. I could have used a little more meat. Then I also had the mac and cheese which was equally as tasteful. The items can be a bit spicy but overall the food was good and if they would just work on better portions they would be my continuous go to spot.
The times I have been the food has been amazing and the service has been very warm and inviting keep it up family I also respect the observe the sabbath and work around that schedule!!
Amazing Food that is enjoyed by DMV residents. Great service. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.
The Salmon tacos and mac and cheese make my soul happy every single time!
FOOD IS SOOOOOOOOOOOOOO BOMB AND ITS NO LONG WAIT🥰💯
Best in the city!!
🔥🔥🔥THE BEST!!! BEEN HOOKED SINCE THE FIRST DAY I HAD IT

They started as a small food truck & now they have a spot ✊🏽 As they should ! Their food is bomb. The tacos are fireeeee. The Mac is everything. They wings are bomb. Everything is ... it’s worth the price. Definitely 💜 the staff is amazing too ☺️
The jerk salmon and Mac and cheese were very flavorful and fresh! I enjoyed every bite of my meal and will be buying more very soon to share with my family! Highly recommended!!!

I have eaten from the truck twice now and everytime it hits the spot!! Both times I went with The Jerk Box N Mac and I know I should try something else but it is SO good. This has definitely become a must have whenever I am in DC now!

Haphazard Covid protocols (at best) - food preparers inside truck maskless or with masks under chin, no signage that patrons need to wear a mask while ordering or waiting.  Kinda defies belief that a small business would operate like this during Covid times.  Until they tighten these things up I am not ordering again.

The jerk Mac is a flavor party in your mouth! Containers are small but it’s LOADED with food! My Husband had the salmon, cabbage with peas and rice. I had the jerk and Mac with a big a$$ piece of Rasta bread. I can only eat half of my meal!
The food was great! It was a little unorganized as far as ordering and pick up. They were also forgetting side items i.e., Coco bread, beef patty. Again, great food!!!

The food was terrible. The plantain was mushy and the beef patty was old and the macaroni was not Caribbean style. The chicken was not Jerk. It was charboil with green,red pepper. Matter fact none of the food is Jamaican style. They need to stop pretending. OMG I'm so upset right now about this food.😡 I had to throw my food away. What a waste of money and still hungry.😖

The macaroni slaps, end of review. The Mac is so delicious they need to change the name to WAP. Delicious! I would pay the delivery fee for just a side of Mac. That said, I also concur about the more spicy than flavorful on other dishes. But will certainly be back.
The Jerk mac and cheese is EVERYTHING!!
Their food is always on point

I’m writing this review mainly after unsatisfactory and I’m my opinion, unacceptable customer service. I ordered a family tray from this restaurant for my birthday as I have been wanting to try it out for a while and in an effort to support black business. Everything was SPICY SPICY SPICY!! I myself am West Indian, from Brooklyn and I’ve never ordered food this spicy without caution or the option of mild and spicy, which is not offered here. My kids could not enjoy anything and my husband barely could leaving me there picking around and trying to cover up the heat in bbq sauce. When I wrote in to DoorDash they suggested I contact the restaurant so I called the number they provided me and no answer. I sent an email, no response. This was overall a very disappointing experience, I could have cooked instead of wasting my money in totality.

The rice and peas were just spicy with no flavor. The mac n cheese didn’t taste like Mac n cheese. The ox tails were super spicy for no reason! The cabbage was too spicy. The bread was decent. West Indian/Caribbean/ Jamaican food is supposed to be savory and flavorful not just spicy!!!!
Order was wrong... Didn’t notice until I was back home in Baltimore... Food was not good at all!!
Customer service was great the food was torch 🤤
Oxtails and Rice
Got it once and the food was great. You can't beat local places with decent prices and large servings.
Best food truck in DC!

Yesterday was my first time trying this spot. I asked for dark meat and they gave me a little of everything. Chicken was dry and some kind of sauce that overpowered the flavor.Waste of good money and I gave a tip. The side of plantains were very tatsty.

I decided to order from Jerk city for a girls night and the rice and beans was rotten , it smelled and tasted like rotten food .the wings were just as nasty . The Mac & cheese was Salty . Honestly the only thing that tasted good was the Chicken . I ordered the Jerk box and the wings and Tingz . I’m disappointed
For $18.00 dollars. All I received on the oxtail dinner was four slices of oxtails and it was mostly bones. Ridiculous!!!!
They have the best chicken tacos. But what happened? There was toping on the tacos, beans and rice? No Bean's.
The place offers a nice variety of delicious food. I enjoy eating here. Staff members are always nice, prices are affordable and the place is always well organised.

The food and quickness of service is great but the customer service need some fine-tuning.  I ordered the jerk chicken soft tacos even though I want it chicken / salmon but was told can't order both can only choose one.  The food was so good that I turned around and ordered $40 worth of food to share with some friends but that was disappointing when I ask for one of the items to have extra jerk sauce and it did not so I asked the order taker for a side of jerk and he told me no "the food has enough on it already".

I ordered the mild chicken wings, plus the Mac& Cheese and Cabbage  had so much sodium in both dishes, I had to throw the food away.  All I could taste was the sodium, which caused my Blood Pressure to skyrocketed.  The rice was not cooked completely, so I had to Microwave it.  If it wasn’t so late on Sunday night, I would have taken the food back and requested a refund.  I wasted $20.00 dollars on this sodium dish.

From the moment  you step in this place  the personel give you an enjoyable feeling. Very courteous hosts, it is a friendly restaurant to  pass time with your friends or with your date. enjoyable  cooking, skillful  chef de cuisine, decent  pay and courteous  service. Highly recommended.
They catered for a party and came on time.  The food was delicious and had plenty of it left over for people to enjoy later.  Some small communication issues, but most were resolved quickly
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I like how the service is always great and they keep the spot neat consistently. Prices are affordable and they serve large portions.
Deliciously good food.  Friendly staff and the jerk seasoning is everything.

I've seen this truck a few times near my office but only on my way back from getting lunch. It seems to arrive around 2pm. One day I happened to leave for lunch when it was there!  I ordered the Jerk Box with Mac and Cheese. The portion was huge, the food was very spicy and delicious!

I have eaten from one of the 2 trucks before (jerk chicken, oxtails, etc) and the food was really good. Today, I'm disappointment at my waste. The chicken is not cooked well to the bone and my cocoa bread is hard enough to be a weapon. I really hate when vendors come out having a good product that is NOT cheap but lines of people and then stop giving people what they were receiving at the start. Unfortunately, I can't return. A wasted $13.  Please don't get comfortable and decrease the appreciated service. Today compares nothing to what I have received. Best wishes to you.
The food is amazing ! You guys are awesome! WE LOVE GETTING JERKED
No Beef Patties No Salmon.  . . Slow service. . .  Let down. .

Placed a large catering order worth $3000 and I was extremely, beyond disappointed. They were over 40 minutes late and without any notice. I was trying hard to track down the caterer and was not receiving any proper update or communication. It threw off my whole event. I will never ever order through this caterer. So unprofessional and unreliable.

This will probably be my last time visiting the food truck. Maybe I'll try their new storefront on H street when it's up & running. Waited in line for over an hour...while in line a man dropped his food (because the wind was blowing about 60mph!!) and they make you bag your own food on a metal ledge that extends from the truck...so it fell to the ground. The owner argued with the customer that he needed to repay for his food after waiting in line for an hour....The man calmly explained to the owner that it was the ledge and the wind that caused the accident....after about 10 mins of arguing, the man ended up having to repay for his fallen food and wait another 20 mins for his order. .obviously policy supersedes service..Totally unacceptable..3 stars because I love my food. The truck was parked at my location by 7am when i arrived at work...so I dont understand why food is not prepped in advance. They begin taking orders at 11:30a. ...I got out there at 11:20a with about 7 people in front of me and did not get my food until 12:55p. DONT plan to go if your workplace doesn't allow leniency for lunch/break..After I finally did get to order, I got my food within 10 mins of waiting..I get the Jerk Mac n Cheese box (jerk mac, jerk chicken + cocoa bread)..... soooo good. and they give a great size portion. All in all, will not be returning until I my craving calls again. Service gets a 1/2 star....

Not bad for my first visit.  But I can only give TrEE Stars Man. The Jerk Wings are good, The Mac and Cheese is very good.  Plantains.... OK. The Coco Bread not to bad.  BUT! that Beef Pattie dog ....... need to soak in some water! I should have taken a picture before throwing it away after 1 bite. I was the driest patty I ever had! I will never buy that again.  After spending $23 (Love supporting our own) I wasn't totally blown But I was.  The Jerk chicken and Mac. Yes Sir!

I want to give them 5 stars on the merit of the food alone. The greatness of the flavor is undeniable. menu is pretty straight forward and I wish this truck came around my way more often. They lose a star because of the occasional longest than expected wait times. It doesn't happen everytime but our would be wrong of me to suggest this hasn't happened. overall though, you will likely be served in a reasonable amount of time. the truck team is friendly and helpful. my photos don't do the food justice at all. the prices are a little high for food trucks but not really high for authentic Caribbean food, the servings are hearty though. I recommend the "jerk box n mac"  20190814 update on this visit my food was excellent as always. the service was lightning fast, less than 3 minutes. The operator said they are working on speed and efficiency. This makes me happy.  Travel and Adventure Influencer IG @brian.dent

Unfortunately, today will have to be my last time supporting you guys. I keep coming back time after time even after being disappointed because the food is good, but you all have to do better with customer service. You all say you will be there at 11:30 but it's rarely the case, the truck may be there and that's it. You have to spend the majority of your lunch hour waiting for the food. The so-called loyalty program needs to be fixed, it should be associated with your phone number and not a card because you may not use the one card every time. And just like today my co-worker used cash and was told she couldn't be given a receipt because it wasn't on a card and she doesn't get any "loyalty points". Lastly, the portion size has gotten smaller but yet we still have to pay the same price. No matter how you try to word saying it's the same amount of food is a lie, an now there is a 10% charge to use a card..... all other food trucks in NOMA use the same system yet no on charges you extra to use a card. It's said when you try to support black businesses and have to deal with so much. Yes, the food is tasty, but the all-around service you receive is not worth it. I'm sure my comment will get deleted, but as a loyal customer I WILL spread the word.
Cabbage wasn't  good. Rice had too much grease nothing like Jamaican Jerk at all
Jerk at night catered a VIP private event. Food was delicious service beyond professional.

The food truck definitely needs some organization. Two stars because while the food was tasty it was full of bone shatters. Had to sieve every bite thru my teeth. Each customer took like two minutes to put an order in with long waits in between while they look for people who ordered. They had to shout over their own music.
Food is good, service not so good! Too bad because I actually enjoyed the taste of the food.  Guy with the dreads rude and seem to not like answering questions about his food or menu..
Best Caribbean food ever !!! The price, the taste... everything perfect
Had the teriyaki salmon with Mac & cheese and coco bread. Everything was delicious!!!!😋😋😋
Great food. Great service. Fun people. The list goes on.
The food was banging. Seasoning great. Friendly service. Hospititable people. I was shocked to get such authentic jamaican food from a food truck
Food is great and I’ll refer everyone black owned and good
Was on Howard University’s campus, and I stumbled upon this food truck...now it’s my favorite thing to eat in DC. Treat ya body rite!
Always sold out and barely available outside of lunch hours. Name should be Jerk @ Noon ( but sold out by 11:30)

I ordered the Kingston Curry, they told me they were out, I was disappointed. Then the guy said hold up let me make you some. It took about 20 min but it well worth it. Made me want to go back last night lol
Great food and service!
When they pick up and are open... 🔥🔥🔥

So many things wrong...  1. Food took forever 2. Only ordered a beef Pattie 3. Ordered from food truck 4. Knew something was wrong when I felt how hard pattie was before I opened bag 5. The aroma that hit my nose 6. The fur on meat on the inside  Yeah that went in the trash... keep the $3.  That is all you'll ever get from me.  Wow!

Came to DC for Broccoli City Fest and had the most horrible customer experience. The workers were slow and uncoordinated. They argued with customers and even went as far as stop taking orders and eating in front of customers face as a provoking joke. I have never experience such terrible service and disappointed for the sake of the Jamaican culture. After a long wait the food was terrible, I only received burnt rice and burnt patties that weren’t fully cooked inside. The owner should be ashamed of the workers at the event. I have video and photos of their behaviors and definitely sharing with the Broccoli City Fest Coordinator so others don’t waste their money here.
The food and the service was excellent and the prices are great.  I will recommend this place if anyone is looking for good food at a great price.
Great food, try to get there before the Howard crowds.

Stopped by their truck for lunch today  - the food was ready in a snap and it was easily the best meal that I had this week in DC.  I had the Jerked Chicken and it was incredible - perfect spicing, and generous portion.  The rice and cabbage were perfect.  It would have been a great meal at twice the price.
Great food!
SAD! Ordered food before the Howard kids got there, was food to wait 15 minutes rice fo be done. Ended up wait 45 minutes! Freezing temps! Rice was mushy! Never again!
Great food - hardly open and difficult to find.
A long wait for inedible food. Rice was burned which made the whole plate smell. Cabbage was not cooked and they served chopped jerk chicken as curry. The worst meal I have had in a long time.
(Translated by Google) Torchhhhh  (Original) Torchhhhh

Was having a great time at the Taste of D.C. until this... after standing in line with my husband and kid for over 45mins for a taste of jerk chicken, the workers at this stand TOTALLY LOST IT!!   Look at her.  She referred to us folks standing in line as a mob, stating they would not serve us unless we figured out how to stand in a line.  I mean they were literally screaming at their patrons.  And there were lots of folks who had been standing in this line for a looooong time.  It's not the customer's fault that yal don't have your s*#! together.  45mins waiting on food at a taste festival is outrageous by itself. Word to the wise to Jerk at Nite in DC- from one business owner to another: learn some customer service.
They never open when it says so, they explain it as if it's my fault they can't get it together. Tighten up.
Great food. Great energy. Great experience.
This food is something serious. The best Jamaican food you'll ever eat.
I never leave D.C. without grabbing a bite first!
Jerk. Chicken. Nachos. Food is tasty, you can taste the quality of the ingredients. Definitely a must-go whenever I'm in the District!
One of the most popular spots in DC with quality food,  professional service & very convenient hours. I would definitely recommend it to anyone in the area.
Amazing
Great food at a great price and they even have a Groupon, Cant beat that!
Amazing food & service! I eat here every chance I get!!
Reallt enjoyed the food. Great customer service, will visit every time I come to DC
Delicious!
Too salty and over priced. Menu said one price and was charged a higher price. Cashier said they need to replace sign. Never ordering again

Jerkatnite is my favorite DC spot. Coming from the south it was difficult to find food with authentic and delicious seasonings. Can you name one other place who serves amazing tacos and superb oxtail? Didn't think so. If you're looking for real food past 10 o'clock or an awesome lunch Jerkatnite is worth the wait.

Great food, but lack basic customer service skills and need more efficient payment systems. Charged me double for an item and would not refund the purchase. The charge didn't match any price point on their menu.

AMAZING jerk chicken and curry chicken are a must have!! Authentic caribbean food with new and innovative flair! Reggae Rasta Pasta with the chicken, onions and grilled peppers are pleasing to any palate. Do yourself a favor and visit this truck sooner rather than later!!
The food was really good! Took a little longer than expected but definitely well worth the wait. I would definitely recommend it to anyone!
Jerk nachos are great!!!
Get the mac & cheese!
(Translated by Google) The jerk box color off!  (Original) The jerk box lit af!
Jerk @ Nite provides quality food for an affordable price. It's great to see black business owners thriving and providing exceptional service

Jerk @ Nite has saved my life on many an occasion man... no one else has jerk chicken like this in DC, you'd be hard pressed to find jerk nachos anywhere else in the city, and the constant innovation of flavors is truly the reason I keep coming back.  In their inception, 8 can say there were some hiccups with the company, but what start up is without opportunities! This company has grown into a mainstay on Howard University's campus- known for its quality food, exceptional service, and great portion sizes.  It's unfortunate that so many of these reviews come from individuals that have seemingly never tried the food at this establishment. To post disparaging comments about a minority owned small businesss during their growth process seems to distract more than it does encourage any further development; let's uplift before we tear down. Give them another chance to turn it around for you! Definitely check it out!

Jerk At Nite has an incredible array of food selections which captured my appetite due to the fact that I love variety. I also love the spices and different flavors they use. Try the jerk chicken - it's lit !!!
